  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      MedlinePlus related topics: Blood Sugar

      Primary Outcome Measures:

        -  Fast glucose and HbA1c change between the baseline and end of study [ Time Frame: From
           baseline to 30 and 100 days]

        -  [ Designated as safety issue: No ]

        -  Successful rate of blood glucose control (the proportion of patients with HbA1c &lt;7%) [
           Time Frame: From baseline to 30 days and 100 days] [ Designated as safety issue: No ]

      Secondary Outcome Measures:

      â€¢ To evaluate the change of quality of life in the 1 months by the health questionnaire SF-36
      [ Time Frame: From baseline to month 1 ] [ Designated as safety issue: No ]
    </textblock>
